Summary: This document contains the timetable for the BA10 FT course, which is part of the Master of Technology in Enterprise Business Analytics program. The course will be taught by lecturers Christine, Dave, and Rita, and will take place from January to May 2024. The course will consist of three days of classes each week, on Mondays, Tuesdays, and Wednesdays from 9:00am to 5:00pm. The document also includes the timetable for the Graduate Certificate in Customer Analytics, which will be taught by Christine, Dave, and Rita as well. The timetable is subject to change and was last updated on February 22, 2024.

The document contains the timetable for the MTech EBAC course for the academic year 2023/2024. The course, titled "Text Processing Using Machine Learning," will be taught by lecturers Aobo and Zhenzhen on various dates throughout February 2024. The course will take place on Mondays, Tuesdays, Wednesdays, Thursdays, and Fridays from 9:00am to 5:00pm. The course is part of the EBA5004 Graduate Certificate in Practical Language Processing and focuses on New Media and Sentiment Mining. The timetable was last updated on 22/2/2024.

The BA10 FT Student Timetable for the AY2023/2024 academic year includes three courses: Complex Predictive Modelling & Forecasting, Product and Pricing Analytics, and Analytics Commercial Excellence. The courses are taught by lecturers Brandon, Christine, Brian, Maowen, David, and Nan Zhou. The classes take place from Monday to Friday, 9:00am-5:00pm, with the first course starting on February 26, 2024 and the last course ending on March 23, 2024. The timetable is subject to change and was last updated on February 22, 2024.

The BA10 FT Student Timetable for the academic year 2023/2024 includes a variety of courses taught by different lecturers on weekdays from 9:00am to 5:00pm. The courses include Data Science Solution Implementation, Processing Big Data for Analytics, EBA5007 Capstone/Internship, Graduate Certificate in Big Data Analytics, and Big Data Engineering for Analytics. Some classes are also scheduled on Saturdays from 9:00am to 5:00pm. The timetable is subject to change and was last updated on 22/2/2024.

The BA10 FT Student Timetable for the academic year 2023/2024 includes several courses such as Credit Risk Modelling and Analytics, Alternative Data for Fintech Innovation, Advanced Machine Learning for Financial Services, and Explainable and Responsible AI for Finance. These courses will be taught by various lecturers including Rita Scott, Brian, Nirmal, Dave, Mao Wen, Vishnu, Christine, and Tian Jing. The timetable shows that the courses will take place on weekdays and Saturdays, from 9:00am to 5:00pm, with a few exceptions. The last update for the timetable was made on 22 February 2024.

The AY2023/2024 Semester 2 Exam Timetable lists the exam dates and times for various graduate certificate courses, including Analytics Project Management, Intelligent Reasoning Systems, Engineering Big Data, Customer Analytics, Intelligent Sensing Systems, Intelligent Software Agents, Securing Ubiquitous Systems, Big Data Analytics, Intelligent Robotic Systems, Architecting Smart Systems, Practical Language Processing, Specialized Predictive Modelling and Forecasting, Business Analytics Practice, Intelligent Financial Risk Management, and Architecting Scalable Systems. The exams will take place on May 13-17, with a range of evening timeslots available. The timetable is subject to change and was last updated on February 22, 2024.
